<p>Arguably, the Foundation could have figured out how to build SRAs from <em>insert SCP here</em>, then figured out humes from studying SRAs. However, SRAs are so hard and expensive to build and maintain, not to mention that you're having to drain the very reality from dead universes, that they can't just be used willy-nilly to neutralize anomalies. However, even though the SRAs aren't available for widespread use, the Foundation now has a system set up for calculating the strength of reality and reality-altering-effects. The way I see it, if they have it, the Foundation will use a scale to measure the strength of magic/science.</p>

