<p>Glad you like it! :D</p>
<p>I actually tried to take the other articles into account when writing this, but then I remembered that &quot;faerie&quot; doesn't actually refer to a single type of creature, but to tons of different types of creatures, so it would make sense that there would be a few skips that could be filed into that category.</p>
<p>I actually figured that it would be applied selectively, considering we have quite a few meta-jokes on the list. Humes are something which I know isn't the most popular but I still have in my headcanon, since I figure that even if SRAs were never widely used, the Foundation would still eventually try to quantify reality and reality bender powers in some form. If you can think of something else which would equate to &quot;oh, and they have an organ which helps give them reality bending powers&quot; I'd be happy to consider changing it. :)</p>
<p>I'm glad that you mentioned the world building, since that had a good chunk of the article's total effort put into it. I'm also hoping to possibly be able to connect a larger network of skips and tales to this later on.</p>
<p>Your voting is understandable. While I did try to make the -J humorous, mainly the researcher's note at the end, it was mostly meant to be another part of the greater story. Also, hey you caught Tamlin!</p>
<p>The Foundation actually tries to capture the -As as soon as it knows that they exist. That's what the MTFs are for, and how we know about their biology and some of their society. I imagine that there might have been one or two points of contact because of the anomaly, but no active attempts to contact Alt!Foundation have been made because the separation of their timelines is shaky at best. I also imagine that some higher ups in Multi-U know about the alternate timeline, but there's no attempts to go there for the same reason. I'm sure that someone on the other end is also trying to stop it, maybe or maybe not the Foundation, but they really couldn't do much. After all, the one thing that keeps our timelines apart is the fact that you don't believe in faeries.</p>

